{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"blue-pig-batch","assignee":"claude","description":"## Why\n\nSupply-chain posture is strong at release (Trusted Publishing / OIDC) but lacks\nthe consumer-facing and preventative pieces popular OSS is expected to carry:\nno SAST, no dependency-vulnerability scanning, and the PyPI attestations the\nrelease action already emits are undocumented. The standard tooling must be\nadapted to this repo's reality: GitHub `main` is a **read-only, Gerrit-gated\nmirror**, so auto-PR mechanisms are dead-ends and a Scorecard badge would\nunder-score by design.\n\n## What\n\n- **CodeQL SAST** — add `.github/workflows/codeql.yml` (Python) running on push\n  to `main` and on a schedule, uploading results to code scanning.\n- **Dependency-vuln scanning** — add a `pip-audit` (or OSV) CI job as a pure\n  check (no merge/PR needed), wired into `.github/workflows/test.yml` or its own\n  workflow.\n- **Alerts, not auto-PRs** — enable/document GitHub + Dependabot **security\n  alerts only** (no version-bump PR config, since GitHub PRs cannot merge here);\n  document in `CONTRIBUTING.md` that dependency bumps land via Gerrit.\n- **Attestations** — verify the release publishes PyPI digital attestations\n  (`pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish@release/v1` + `id-token: write`, attestations\n  on by default) and document how consumers verify them (e.g. in\n  `docs/releasing.md`).\n\n## Scope\n\n`.github/workflows/*` (CodeQL + pip-audit), plus doc notes in `docs/releasing.md`\n/ `CONTRIBUTING.md`. Explicitly OUT: OpenSSF Scorecard badge/workflow, SBOM, and\nDependabot version-update PRs (all deferred per the epic's OUT list).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `.github/workflows/codeql.yml` runs CodeQL for Python and uploads results.\n- [ ] A `pip-audit`/OSV dependency-scan job runs in CI as a check.\n- [ ] Docs state that only security ALERTS are used (no auto-PRs) and that bumps\n  land via Gerrit.\n- [ ] `docs/releasing.md` documents the emitted PyPI attestations and how to\n  verify them; a released artifact is confirmed to expose attestations.\n- [ ] New workflows are green; no Scorecard badge, SBOM, or Dependabot PR config\n  is added.","id":"95dc-cbe7-ed1d-48dc","parent_id":"b02d-10bc-07ee-49e7","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Supply-chain CI hardening: CodeQL SAST, pip-audit scan, alerts, attestation docs"},"env_id":"58e9f32e-f999-436d-9c1a-5d0eef5c9903","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783148928897206479,"uuid":"841f9cf6-c8dc-4806-887b-28994ed78290"}